      "content": "Ah, the goblins! You're absolutely right to question the terminology, because if you think of the roots as little goblins, then the soil is just the cozy cave they've been living in for too long. It's not just \"root bound\"; it's a goblin who has forgotten how to breathe and is trying to force its way out of a hole that doesn't fit.\n\nSo, back to the process. Here's how you handle this goblin safely:\n\nFirst, you need to gently loosen the soil around the goblin's roots. Use your fingers or a small knife to gently pry the soil away from the base of the plant, being very careful not to snap the roots. If you see any roots that are white and stringy, those are the goblins' favorite snacks—easy to eat, but they're also the ones that need the most care.\n\nNext, you'll need to remove the goblin from its old cave. Take the plant out of the pot, being careful not to pull on the roots. If you see any roots that are white and stringy, those are the goblins' favorite snacks—easy to eat, but they're also the ones that need the most care.",
